# Downloads and local vs remote playback

Apply when editing download stores, playback URL resolution, or offline behavior.

## URL resolution

In **`songToTrack(song)`** (`hooks/useAudioStore.ts`):

- `localUri = song.localUri || useMusicDownloadsStore.getState().getLocalUri(song.id)`.
- `url = localUri || (song.uri if non-empty)`.
- Local always wins when available. Plex music bitrate / `buildPlexStreamUrl` applies only when **not** local and **not** podcast (see `plex-streaming-urls` rule).

## Download bitrates

- Music downloads use **`downloadBitrateKbps`** from playback settings and **`buildPlexStreamUrl`** in `useMusicDownloadsStore` when fetching the file.

## Podcasts

- Episodes get `localUri` or stream URL at call sites (`toPlayableSong` in types/podcast, feed/episode screens, `PodcastEpisodeItem`).
- Resume: downloaded episodes use `usePodcastDownloadsStore.getState().getResumeAt(song.id)`; streamed use the progress store.
- Progress is saved to both progress store and (when downloaded) `updateResumeAt`.

## Offline

- `useOfflineModeStore` and `useOfflineFilteredLibrary` restrict library UI to downloaded content.
- Playback does not branch on “offline mode”; it uses whatever URL `songToTrack` resolves. With offline mode on, the filtered library should only surface items with local playability.
